HEADWORD: Torvous
<hw>Tor"vous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>torvus</ets>. ]</ety> <def>Sour of aspect; of a severe countenance;
stern; grim.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>torvous</qex>, sour look produced by anger.</q>
<rj><qau>Derham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tory</ent>⟦br⟧
